CC  Chaperones the DNA polymerase holoenzyme (CPX-1924) to the replication
CC  fork in an ATP-dependent manner. Each of the three gamma/tau subunits
CC  (P06710) can bind one molecule of ATP but the binding of a single
CC  molecule of ATP per complex is sufficient. Binding of ATP opens the
CC  pentameric ring of DnaX (see below) and allows interaction with the
CC  open beta subunit sliding clamp (CPX-1927). Subsequent attachment of
CC  the template-primer DNA to the pentameric ring triggers hydrolysis and
CC  detachment of the DnaX complex from the beta clamp-DNA complex
CC  (CPX-1927). The beta clamp closes and facilitates strand elongation via
CC  the DNA polymerase III core subcomplex (CPX-1925).
